Eastern Cape police have confirmed the body of one of the missing Maredon fishermen was located.The remains of Mbongeni Gift Zulu, 43, of Jeffreys Bay, were found floating in the sea near Blue Horizon Bay in Port Elizabeth.The fishermen went missing when a chokka fishing boat capsized near Thyspunt on Saturday and only ran aground near St Francis on Sunday morning.It is believed that 16 people were in the boat at the time it capsized, seven fishermen are still missing.On Sunday, police divers, National Sea Rescue Institute (NSRI) and other role players rescued six fishermen and recovered a body of a man.The survivors are still recovering in hospital and police have opened an inquest docket for investigation.-TNA Reporter